Note: On August 1, 2024, you can no longer use externally built machine learning models in Einstein Discovery. Instead, use Einstein Discovery to create a model.

Set Up Your Development Environment for Machine Learning Models

Your development environment must include Python 3.7 and either TensorFlow 2.7.0 or Scikit-learn 1.0.2. Additional libraries are supported of specified versions only.

Prepare the Upload File for the Machine Learning Model

After building the machine learning model in your development environment, prepare an upload .zip file that meets all the requirements.
